                </summary>
                <p class="text-[#4e4538] text-sm leading-loose mt-4 pr-8">
                  Frigiliana offers the best of both worlds: mountain calm and coastal access. The village is about 6–7 km from the sea. It takes roughly 10–12 minutes to drive to the beaches of Nerja. There is also a regular bus service connecting the village to the coast.
                </p>
              </details>

              {/* FAQ 5 */}
              <details class="group border-b border-[#d2c5b3]/30 py-6 cursor-pointer [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
                <summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-[#1b1c1a] outline-none">
                  Are shops open on Sundays?
                  <span class="text-[#785611] text-xl group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-300">+</span>
                </summary>
                <p class="text-[#4e4538] text-sm leading-loose mt-4 pr-8">
                  Tourist shops and restaurants remain open. Standard grocery stores and pharmacies are usually closed or have reduced hours.
                </p>
              </details>

              {/* FAQ 6 */}
